Class RGB

public final class RGB
extends Object
implements org.eclipse.swt.internal.SerializableCompatibility

Safe: Instances of this class are descriptions of colors in terms of the primary additive color model (red, green and blue). A color may be described in terms of the relative intensities of these three primary colors. The brightness of each color is specified by a value in the range 0 to 255, where 0 indicates no color (blackness) and 255 indicates maximum intensity.

Application code does not need to explicitly release the resources managed by each instance when those instances are no longer required, and thus no dispose() method is provided.
